sensitivity options for that are a pain. Also I recommend adding two player 
mode over LAN. Online is an undertaking and I get that, but 2 player option 
with the people I get into this game, would give it so much sharability.
replyContent: Tim, thanks for the review. Did you know...that you don't have to press the button on the screen to turn - the whole left and right edges of the screen will accept the touch input. The graphic is just there as a guide. The weapon buttons are offset from those edges so you don't accidentally hit them in the heat of battle.
